## ✅ Improvements Made — Summary

Here's a complete list of all issues found and fixed across the code-review-team:

### 📁 YAML Structural Fixes (4 files)

| File | Issue | Fix |
|------|-------|-----|
| `recipe/code-review-team.yaml` | **Missing `name` field** | Added `name: Code Review Team — Orchestrator` |
| `recipe/code-review-team.yaml` | `max_steps: 100` → should be `max_turns` | Changed to `max_turns: 100` |
| All 3 sub YAMLs | `max_steps: 30` → should be `max_turns` | Changed to `max_turns: 30` |
| All 4 YAMLs | `goose_provider`/`goose_model` → non-standard field names | Changed to standard `provider`/`model` |

### 🗣️ Prompt & Agent Identity Fixes (4 files)

| File | Issue | Fix |
|------|-------|-----|
| All 3 sub YAMLs | **MODE-CHECK prefix** leaked orchestrator identity into sub-agents (e.g., `I am static-analyzer ... MODE-CHECK: code-review-team`) | Clean prompts now start with agent identity and describe their task |
| `static-analyzer.yaml` | **Contradictory rule**: prompt said `⛔ NO YAML/JSON/MD edits` but instructions explicitly tell it to output JSON | Removed the contradictory rule |
| `code-review-team.yaml` | Vague 1-line prompt just repeated the title | Replaced with actionable description of the delegation workflow |
| `code-review-team.yaml` | Rules R01-R04 were generic/didn't enforce parallel execution | Added specific rules: R02 (must run PARALLEL), R03 (collect both results before delegating to code-reviewer) |

### 🔍 Static Analyzer — `static-analyzer.md` (3 fixes)

| Fix | Detail |
|-----|--------|
| **Severity mapping added** | Lint results now map `ERROR→P1`, `WARNING→P2`, `INFO→P3`, `STYLE→P4`, `NOTE→P5` where previously there was no mapping |
| **P4/P5 output support** | `observations` severity now includes P4/P5; `overview` now tracks `p4_count` and `p5_count` |
| **Over-broad `print(` check** | Changed from blanket `grep -rn 'print('` to flag only `print(` statements outside CLI entry points or logging contexts |

### 🛡️ Security Scanner — `security-scanner.md` (1 fix)

| Fix | Detail |
|-----|--------|
| **`%s` pattern gap in SQLI-003** | Original regex `%s*\(` only matched dict-style `%(name)s` formatting, missing simple `%s` formatting like `execute("SELECT * FROM %s WHERE id = %s" % (table, id))`. Changed to `%s*` which catches both patterns |

### 📋 Code Reviewer — `code-reviewer.md` (2 fixes)

| Fix | Detail |
|-----|--------|
| **Unused `syntax_errors` variable** | Variable `syntax_errors` was computed but never referenced in the decision if/elif chain. Renamed to `has_syntax_errors` and integrated into the `request_changes` logic for critical syntax issues |
| **`recommendations` schema mismatch** | Schema said `recommendations: [string]` (array of strings) but actual output uses objects with `priority`, `finding`, `action`, `note` fields. Updated schema to match the real structure |

### ✅ Validation

All 4 YAML files (`code-review-team.yaml`, `static-analyzer.yaml`, `security-scanner.yaml`, `code-reviewer.yaml`) pass YAML validation and have correct field names (`max_turns`, `provider`, `model`).
